WEBVTT

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:15.600
Subtitle Provide by dramacool.asia Translator [Admin.@YNG]

00:00:25.030 --> 00:00:27.430
(Song Joong Ki)

00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:34.140
(Chun Woo Hee)

00:00:34.910 --> 00:00:36.570
(Lee Joo Myung)

00:00:37.310 --> 00:00:38.580
(Seo Ji Hun)

00:00:45.820 --> 00:00:50.960
(My Youth)

00:01:00.030 --> 00:01:01.330
I'd be lying...

00:01:02.470 --> 00:01:06.300
if I said I never thought about you.

00:01:08.370 --> 00:01:09.570
Quite the opposite.

00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.340
Like an overplayed cassette tape,

00:01:14.310 --> 00:01:17.350
I'd replay those moments in my head until they were completely worn out.

00:01:20.020 --> 00:01:21.420
Seeing you again,

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:25.760
you instantly took me right back to that time.

00:01:27.190 --> 00:01:28.890
As if teasing me.

00:01:33.830 --> 00:01:35.600
When I could find nothing...

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:38.440
to refer to in any of the pages.

00:01:38.970 --> 00:01:39.970
To that time.

00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:57.920
My path wasn't so dark.

00:02:00.530 --> 00:02:01.530
Thanks to you.

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:11.969
Team Leader Sung Je Yeon, the next script.

00:02:11.970 --> 00:02:12.970
Yes.

00:02:12.971 --> 00:02:14.939
It's a historical fantasy romance.

00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:16.069
It's pre-produced for streaming,

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:18.239
and it's Director Han Seok Won's first series.

00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:20.409
It's based on the folktale, "The Fairy and the Woodcutter."

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:22.150
The main character is a palace seamstress.

00:02:22.410 --> 00:02:25.019
She enters an embroidery competition at the palace,

00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:27.820
and the clothing is stolen by the woodcutter, the male lead...

00:02:28.290 --> 00:02:29.849
Isn't he just a straight-up thief?

00:02:29.850 --> 00:02:31.660
Well, the woodcutter was a thief in the original story, too.

00:02:32.020 --> 00:02:33.419
Who's in talks for the male lead again?

00:02:33.420 --> 00:02:34.759
Pyo Mun Su.

00:02:34.760 --> 00:02:37.899
He was a top model, and this is his acting debut.

00:02:37.900 --> 00:02:40.769
Well, good for him for trying. Tell him to work hard. Next.

00:02:40.770 --> 00:02:43.029
This next one is an in-house project.

00:02:43.030 --> 00:02:45.369
It's from "The Sun and the Moon," the "give-me-a-rice-cake" story.

00:02:45.370 --> 00:02:46.440
You all know that one, right?

00:02:46.970 --> 00:02:48.670
I thought the premise for this one was interesting.

00:02:49.110 --> 00:02:51.509
Turning "The Sun and the Moon" into a space opera is quite a take.

00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:55.480
But isn't the concept a little too much?

00:02:56.810 --> 00:02:58.779
What is this guy, a complete pig?

00:02:58.780 --> 00:03:00.819
He's not a tiger, is he? He's a pig.

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:03.019
And he's in a time loop just to keep eating rice cakes?

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:05.190
- Just how many is he scarfing down? - They must have been tasty.

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:08.459
Visit the set for a day and give notes on the rice cake scenes.

00:03:08.460 --> 00:03:11.060
Get Hae Yeong in here for this one and have her read it by today.

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:13.570
And have Tae Rin do the daily drama.

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:18.099
Ma'am, that doesn't start filming for another month.

00:03:18.100 --> 00:03:20.139
And she's not even done with her current project.

00:03:20.140 --> 00:03:22.109
Once she's done with her current project,

00:03:22.110 --> 00:03:24.309
shouldn't she get to take a bit of a break?

00:03:24.310 --> 00:03:28.479
She's an adult, on her third series. We need to solidify her brand...

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:30.320
What, did you two rehearse this?

00:03:31.450 --> 00:03:34.120
We're not that close, ma'am.

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:39.660
Let's move on.

00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:50.170
Excuse me, ma'am.

00:03:50.940 --> 00:03:52.469
Don't get the wrong idea.

00:03:52.470 --> 00:03:55.039
It's just that Tae Rin has only been doing historical dramas,

00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:57.279
and since this is her first contemporary role,

00:03:57.280 --> 00:03:59.279
I was hoping she could shed that typecast image.

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:00.310
Is he your boyfriend?

00:04:00.710 --> 00:04:02.779
The guy whose clothes you ripped in front of the office yesterday.

00:04:02.780 --> 00:04:04.280
Oh, him...

00:04:05.320 --> 00:04:08.520
I apologise for causing a scene in front of the office.

00:04:09.450 --> 00:04:10.920
Was that too personal?

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:13.760
I thought we were close enough, Je Yeon.

00:04:14.330 --> 00:04:15.429
Well...

00:04:15.430 --> 00:04:18.159
The man from yesterday... His name is Sunwoo Hae.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:20.300
Does that name ring a bell?

00:04:21.430 --> 00:04:22.430
I see.

00:04:24.300 --> 00:04:25.670
Let's see, what was he in?

00:04:26.170 --> 00:04:28.239
Beat or Bebop or something? That kid?

00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:30.140
Oh, of course, you remember.

00:04:30.440 --> 00:04:33.409
Tae Rin and I actually went to the same school as him,

00:04:33.410 --> 00:04:35.210
and my senior colleague, So Ra, asked me for a favour...

00:04:35.750 --> 00:04:38.219
Producer Jin So Ra. We went to college together.

00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:40.179
That award-winning pilot was her debut. I know her.

00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:41.819
Yes, with her,

00:04:41.820 --> 00:04:43.759
that two-part documentary that got shelved last year...

00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:45.420
I was thinking we could try and revive it.

00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:47.330
It would be a short shoot,

00:04:47.830 --> 00:04:51.599
and it's rare to find a nice project that isn't chasing sensationalism.

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:53.400
You really like "nice" projects, don't you, Team Leader Sung?

00:04:53.900 --> 00:04:54.900
Draft up a proposal.

00:04:54.901 --> 00:04:56.100
Thank you, ma'am.

00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:00.670
What a relief.

00:05:04.380 --> 00:05:06.710
"I'm really sorry, but..."

00:05:07.180 --> 00:05:09.349
"Hearing you call me takes me back."

00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:11.780
"You only call me sir these days."

00:05:12.420 --> 00:05:14.250
"You really haven't changed a bit."

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:15.820
All done?

00:05:16.820 --> 00:05:18.189
- Yes. - Want to take a quick break?

00:05:18.190 --> 00:05:20.060
- Sounds good. - Oh, sure.

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:25.929
Well...

00:05:25.930 --> 00:05:28.299
You know the screenwriter, Ahn So Jin, right?

00:05:28.300 --> 00:05:30.440
Everything she writes gets over 30 percent in ratings.

00:05:30.870 --> 00:05:32.499
"My Annoying Daughter"

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:34.209
That title is so annoying.

00:05:34.210 --> 00:05:35.709
Do people even say "annoying" anymore?

00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:37.910
The only slight issue is,

00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:39.209
the shoot starts in a month,

00:05:39.210 --> 00:05:41.980
and it's 50 episodes, so it'll be a physical grind.

00:05:43.010 --> 00:05:45.679
But didn't you say you were tired of historical dramas?

00:05:45.680 --> 00:05:47.950
This is a contemporary story, set in the 2020s.

00:05:48.320 --> 00:05:50.660
So this is what all my offers are like now?

00:05:51.360 --> 00:05:52.390
Starting in a month...

00:05:53.060 --> 00:05:54.360
I wonder how many people passed on this.

00:05:55.860 --> 00:05:59.099
If you're up for it, instead of "My Annoying Daughter,"

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:01.969
I think the two-part documentary might be a better option.

00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:04.200
You know, the one with Sunwoo Hae back then.

00:06:04.540 --> 00:06:06.140
You know the project doesn't work without you.

00:06:07.340 --> 00:06:08.640
It couldn't happen without me?

00:06:09.340 --> 00:06:12.040
It was scrapped without Sunwoo Hae, but now that he's found, it'll work.

00:06:15.680 --> 00:06:16.750
Tae Rin.

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:18.880
Hey, Tae Rin.

00:06:29.530 --> 00:06:31.330
Where are you going by yourself?

00:06:32.130 --> 00:06:33.430
To go buy bubbles.

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.030
I saw a stationery shop nearby.

00:06:36.870 --> 00:06:39.640
If you want to go for a smoke, I already found a hidden spot.

00:06:44.110 --> 00:06:47.380
Why do I feel like blowing bubbles right now of all times?

00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:54.690
I know you're worried about them dredging up the "child actor" thing.

00:06:58.490 --> 00:06:59.720
"She's not as good as she was as a kid."

00:07:00.020 --> 00:07:01.729
"She's stuck in her childhood roles."

00:07:01.730 --> 00:07:03.130
This project is perfect for that.

00:07:03.930 --> 00:07:06.399
Even at my age, whatever I do, I still get the "child actor" label.

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:07.599
It makes me want to throw up.

00:07:07.600 --> 00:07:10.870
A nostalgic trip with the co-star who's the very symbol of that label?

00:07:12.340 --> 00:07:13.639
Isn't that just torture?

00:07:13.640 --> 00:07:15.570
But the person you were back then is still a part of you.

00:07:16.210 --> 00:07:19.310
I thought you were amazing then, and you're still amazing now.

00:07:19.910 --> 00:07:20.910
What was that?

00:07:21.610 --> 00:07:24.020
You're not the type to say cheesy things like that, Je Yeon.

00:07:24.850 --> 00:07:25.850
Did you get struck by lightning?

00:07:25.851 --> 00:07:27.050
Should I go get struck by it now?

00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:38.830
Gosh. You're so cute, you almost had me there.

00:07:41.570 --> 00:07:43.130
My true self...

00:07:44.540 --> 00:07:45.969
I don't have the confidence to show it.

00:07:45.970 --> 00:07:49.469
Don't draw such a hard line. Why not blend them a little?

00:07:49.470 --> 00:07:50.810
I mean, it's all scripted anyway.

00:07:52.040 --> 00:07:54.509
You could just add a little extra something.

00:07:54.510 --> 00:07:55.680
What would you mix in?

00:07:57.550 --> 00:08:00.279
My wisdom and sagacity?

00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:02.050
That's a brilliant idea.

00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:04.790
You can be anything you want to be.

00:08:08.630 --> 00:08:10.160
But what's the deal with Sunwoo Hae?

00:08:10.460 --> 00:08:11.860
I thought he said he wouldn't do it.

00:08:12.360 --> 00:08:13.430
Who knows.

00:08:13.870 --> 00:08:15.670
He must have had a change of heart.

00:08:16.670 --> 00:08:18.800
Apparently, he wants to get rich.

00:08:28.080 --> 00:08:29.250
Feeling a little better?

00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:31.850
Should I give you some space?

00:08:32.620 --> 00:08:33.920
Come with me.

00:08:40.290 --> 00:08:42.360
Did you have a price range in mind?

00:08:43.490 --> 00:08:46.059
To make a full bouquet with the flowers you've chosen,

00:08:46.060 --> 00:08:48.699
it would be around 70 dollars.

00:08:48.700 --> 00:08:50.130
Could you make it 50, please?

00:08:50.570 --> 00:08:51.970
I can't spend more than that. Not on that...

00:08:53.470 --> 00:08:54.670
That person.

00:08:56.470 --> 00:08:57.780
I'll make sure it looks full.

00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:00.210
But...

00:09:00.610 --> 00:09:03.450
You broke up, but he invited you to his solo exhibition?

00:09:04.450 --> 00:09:06.480
I wonder if this is what he's trying to say.

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:08.189
"A new beginning."

00:09:08.190 --> 00:09:10.019
No, I don't want a new beginning with him.

00:09:10.020 --> 00:09:11.020
I see.

00:09:12.120 --> 00:09:13.120
Okay.

00:09:14.790 --> 00:09:15.790
"The impossible."

00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:17.959
I'll make this work for 50 dollars.

00:09:17.960 --> 00:09:20.030
You've become a smooth operator.

00:09:26.040 --> 00:09:27.040
What?

00:09:27.470 --> 00:09:28.810
It's adorable.

00:09:38.980 --> 00:09:40.420
I hope it makes a great gift.

00:09:41.120 --> 00:09:43.120
- Please come again. - Thank you.

00:09:48.490 --> 00:09:49.890
You're a natural at sales.

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:54.570
What?

00:09:58.800 --> 00:09:59.970
You look pretty today.

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:08.009
I came here to ask you something, and I almost forgot what it was.

00:10:08.010 --> 00:10:10.010
Is your beauty that shocking?

00:10:10.880 --> 00:10:13.320
You've got a certain presence about you.

00:10:13.820 --> 00:10:16.350
- What? - For one, you know flower meanings.

00:10:17.220 --> 00:10:18.459
That?

00:10:18.460 --> 00:10:19.959
I read this book until it fell apart.

00:10:19.960 --> 00:10:22.330
It was on their origins and history.

00:10:22.460 --> 00:10:23.830
To think you never cracked a book for school.

00:10:25.360 --> 00:10:27.369
I just wonder, why do people buy flowers?

00:10:27.370 --> 00:10:28.629
Hey, now.

00:10:28.630 --> 00:10:30.100
That's a bit harsh.

00:10:30.770 --> 00:10:33.040
- Why won't they? - Of course, they buy them.

00:10:33.570 --> 00:10:34.770
Just not for themselves.

00:10:35.440 --> 00:10:38.179
They're always going to performances to congratulate people.

00:10:38.180 --> 00:10:39.210
Tae Rin does, too.

00:10:43.510 --> 00:10:45.849
Since blue roses don't occur naturally...

00:10:45.850 --> 00:10:47.590
they were originally a symbol of the impossible.

00:10:48.350 --> 00:10:51.659
But once genetically engineered, their meaning changed.

00:10:51.660 --> 00:10:53.059
So what did it change to?

00:10:53.060 --> 00:10:54.429
Curious enough to buy one and find out?

00:10:54.430 --> 00:10:55.629
And do what with it?

00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:57.230
You can figure that out after you buy it.

00:11:00.700 --> 00:11:02.170
That sounded too much like a sales pitch, didn't it?

00:11:03.870 --> 00:11:06.799
No, I mean, who gave flowers their meanings in the first place?

00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:08.309
The people trying to sell them, of course.

00:11:08.310 --> 00:11:09.870
Exactly. For whose benefit?

00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:12.380
The florists, that's who.

00:11:15.910 --> 00:11:17.450
Anyway, about the shoot...

00:11:18.050 --> 00:11:20.850
Let's just say we're old high school friends.

00:11:21.320 --> 00:11:23.219
- So you play along. - And what should I say?

00:11:23.220 --> 00:11:25.020
That we're high school friends who kissed?

00:11:27.790 --> 00:11:28.830
Hey, you!

00:11:29.390 --> 00:11:30.430
Hey.

00:11:30.660 --> 00:11:32.730
Technically, that's not what happened, all right?

00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:34.629
It wasn't, but if you say anything...

00:11:34.630 --> 00:11:36.270
I'm not kidding, you'll regret it.

00:11:38.100 --> 00:11:40.340
You pick the date for the meeting. Any day works.

00:11:41.740 --> 00:11:43.809
I've decided to get along with you.

00:11:43.810 --> 00:11:45.140
At least until filming is over.

00:11:45.540 --> 00:11:46.679
Let's not get on each other's nerves.

00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:48.009
Depends on how you act.

00:11:48.010 --> 00:11:50.010
You might even end up respecting me.

00:11:59.460 --> 00:12:00.660
Look at you.

00:12:01.990 --> 00:12:03.190
Take a good long look.

00:12:04.200 --> 00:12:05.200
All right.

00:12:07.500 --> 00:12:08.500
I'm off.

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:12.040
Go on, then.

00:12:18.680 --> 00:12:19.680
Welcome.

00:12:24.010 --> 00:12:25.349
Here for some flowers?

00:12:25.350 --> 00:12:28.249
Yes. I'm just going to browse for a bit.

00:12:28.250 --> 00:12:29.250
I'm waiting for someone.

00:12:29.251 --> 00:12:31.320
Oh, of course. Take your time.

00:12:40.230 --> 00:12:41.599
Excuse me, are you a producer?

00:12:41.600 --> 00:12:43.200
Me? Yes.

00:12:44.200 --> 00:12:45.969
- What? - Hey.

00:12:45.970 --> 00:12:48.269
- Oh, you're here. - Sung Je Yeon.

00:12:48.270 --> 00:12:50.739
Where is he? I said, where is he?

00:12:50.740 --> 00:12:52.709
If you're messing with me,

00:12:52.710 --> 00:12:54.510
I swear, you're going to pay for this.

00:12:54.750 --> 00:12:56.749
You want to know why? Because yesterday,

00:12:56.750 --> 00:12:59.649
- I pulled an all-nighter, you hear? - The coffee! Over there.

00:12:59.650 --> 00:13:01.120
It's Sunwoo Hae. Right there.

00:13:01.550 --> 00:13:02.690
Right there.

00:13:07.320 --> 00:13:09.730
I said any day, and you really took me up on it right away.

00:13:11.830 --> 00:13:13.499
Hello, I'm Sunwoo Hae.

00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:14.700
Wait, what's this? What happened?

00:13:18.070 --> 00:13:19.169
I'm Jin So Ra.

00:13:19.170 --> 00:13:20.599
Gosh!

00:13:20.600 --> 00:13:22.440
I wasn't expecting to meet you like this.

00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:23.909
Gosh!

00:13:23.910 --> 00:13:26.639
Look how much you've grown!

00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:29.279
I mean it, you're huge! Bebop, you used to be this tiny.

00:13:29.280 --> 00:13:30.550
And now you're all grown up...

00:13:31.220 --> 00:13:34.390
I was a huge fan of "Beat and Bebop"

00:13:35.850 --> 00:13:37.890
Who knew I'd get so big, right?

00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:41.789
Anyway, thank you for coming.

00:13:41.790 --> 00:13:42.989
No, I should be thanking you.

00:13:42.990 --> 00:13:44.859
No, really, thank you.

00:13:44.860 --> 00:13:46.100
Oh, my gosh!

00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:48.429
Oh, I...

00:13:48.430 --> 00:13:51.370
I have to put my project on hold and revise this segment.

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:54.439
This project is really important to me.

00:13:54.440 --> 00:13:56.870
Please don't change your mind.

00:13:58.080 --> 00:13:59.780
Then make me not want to.

00:14:01.080 --> 00:14:03.709
Right, I just stepped out for a moment.

00:14:03.710 --> 00:14:06.879
If any issues come up, Je Yeon here will be in touch.

00:14:06.880 --> 00:14:08.220
Okay.

00:14:08.720 --> 00:14:09.750
See you soon.

00:14:10.390 --> 00:14:12.160
Leaving? I'll go with you.

00:14:18.160 --> 00:14:19.260
Let's do a great job.

00:14:20.600 --> 00:14:22.430
Hey, Sung Je Yeon.

00:14:29.270 --> 00:14:32.110
She just comes and goes as she pleases.

00:14:32.680 --> 00:14:33.880
Always doing whatever she wants.

00:14:40.850 --> 00:14:41.990
You called for me?

00:14:42.190 --> 00:14:43.220
Hi.

00:14:43.320 --> 00:14:44.790
Looks like you set our meetings to overlap.

00:14:45.190 --> 00:14:46.690
I got here a little early.

00:14:46.990 --> 00:14:48.259
Should I give you two some space?

00:14:48.260 --> 00:14:49.830
I read the report you submitted.

00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.560
But you left out the issue with Yu Je Il.

00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:53.430
We're currently coordinating a meeting date.

00:14:53.830 --> 00:14:56.430
And as for "My Annoying Daughter," the filming schedule...

00:14:56.800 --> 00:14:59.500
I decided the schedule would be too physically demanding for her.

00:14:59.770 --> 00:15:01.439
This is Tae Rin's first documentary.

00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:04.070
Does she have to share the spotlight with some non-celebrity?

00:15:04.540 --> 00:15:05.879
I have a feeling once this airs,

00:15:05.880 --> 00:15:07.380
people will talk more about Sunwoo Hae.

00:15:08.610 --> 00:15:11.550
Because he's been off the radar since he was 13.

00:15:11.850 --> 00:15:13.350
Because he vanished so dramatically.

00:15:13.720 --> 00:15:14.990
Which makes people curious.

00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:18.760
Since he's a non-celebrity, it's hard to create follow-up buzz,

00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:21.290
so I prioritised Tae Rin.

00:15:22.030 --> 00:15:25.100
Because that's what's best for the company and for you, ma'am.

00:15:25.400 --> 00:15:28.999
Why would he bother to be on TV now at his age?

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:30.870
It makes you wonder. Is it for the money?

00:15:32.370 --> 00:15:33.699
Just give me your approval,

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:36.140
and I'll be on set for every shoot and handle everything personally.

00:15:38.540 --> 00:15:40.440
Don't let him get too close to Tae Rin.

00:15:40.640 --> 00:15:43.310
And don't let him pull any stunts for a comeback or personal gain.

00:15:43.710 --> 00:15:45.820
You brought him in, so it's on you to keep him in line.

00:15:46.150 --> 00:15:48.190
And keep a close eye on Sunwoo Hae during the entire shoot.

00:15:49.020 --> 00:15:50.850
Yes, ma'am.

00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:01.699
Mom, why have you always hated him so much?

00:16:01.700 --> 00:16:03.930
I have? When? Just now?

00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:05.769
Why on earth would I hate him?

00:16:05.770 --> 00:16:07.640
If it's a good idea, why not just do it?

00:16:08.710 --> 00:16:09.840
Do his motives really matter?

00:16:14.350 --> 00:16:15.410
That's a good point.

00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:18.650
You're pretty sharp.

00:16:25.090 --> 00:16:27.730
There it is. That prickly side.

00:16:29.030 --> 00:16:30.890
I'm so sick and tired of it.

00:16:53.250 --> 00:16:54.950
He looks worse in person than on TV.

00:17:00.790 --> 00:17:02.490
Hey, what are we going to do?

00:17:03.090 --> 00:17:04.459
The baby just won't cry.

00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:05.629
Tell me about it.

00:17:05.630 --> 00:17:07.500
He has to cry for us to use the footage.

00:17:13.070 --> 00:17:15.340
Excuse me! Coming through. Hey!

00:17:20.410 --> 00:17:22.610
- A debt collector? - Hey, get the shot! Quick!

00:17:32.790 --> 00:17:35.560
You should've paid me back!

00:17:37.030 --> 00:17:38.430
Sunwoo Hae's story...

00:17:39.130 --> 00:17:41.170
is ideal for gossip, don't you think?

00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:44.400
He was the face of that fraud case.

00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:47.840
His mother even took her own life because she lost hope.

00:17:54.610 --> 00:17:55.680
So?

00:17:56.980 --> 00:17:58.080
What are you so worried about?

00:17:58.950 --> 00:18:00.020
It's just...

00:18:00.950 --> 00:18:03.590
It seems good, even to me, but I'm worried it'll get tainted.

00:18:05.290 --> 00:18:06.320
You know, Mom,

00:18:06.520 --> 00:18:08.589
you sound like you're talking about Sunwoo Hae when he was 13.

00:18:08.590 --> 00:18:09.860
The way you feel sorry for him.

00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:11.960
I do?

00:18:12.900 --> 00:18:14.469
Pity him? Why would I?

00:18:14.470 --> 00:18:17.670
Thinking only of your actress, this is a great opportunity.

00:18:18.370 --> 00:18:21.670
People who watch the show will say that Mo Tae Rin turned out so well.

00:18:21.840 --> 00:18:23.040
All thanks to Sunwoo Hae.

00:18:23.540 --> 00:18:25.040
But that's not what you were just thinking, was it?

00:18:26.880 --> 00:18:28.810
It's as if you've gone back to that time.

00:18:32.820 --> 00:18:34.220
This documentary is going to be a hit.

00:18:36.090 --> 00:18:38.220
I've got to go. I need to get back to the office.

00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.599
Art Director!

00:18:44.600 --> 00:18:45.930
Excuse me, coming through.

00:18:53.200 --> 00:18:55.640
Producer, you said today was just supposed to be our first meeting.

00:18:56.770 --> 00:18:58.880
But you show up with cameras and a whole crew...

00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:02.480
We're doing two things at once. To save some time.

00:19:02.680 --> 00:19:06.079
We figured we could get a little screen test done while we're at it.

00:19:06.080 --> 00:19:07.080
Hello.

00:19:07.081 --> 00:19:08.990
I'm Jung Ji Hye, the writer for the show.

00:19:09.220 --> 00:19:10.220
Hello.

00:19:10.221 --> 00:19:11.789
And this is our junior writer.

00:19:11.790 --> 00:19:12.790
Hello.

00:19:12.791 --> 00:19:14.090
I trust you've seen the proposal?

00:19:14.290 --> 00:19:16.859
Yes, but I must admit I didn't quite understand what it was about.

00:19:16.860 --> 00:19:18.699
Well, that's the thing about television.

00:19:18.700 --> 00:19:22.070
Until it actually airs, no one knows how it will turn out.

00:19:22.270 --> 00:19:24.799
Let's get shots of the inside. What are you waiting for?

00:19:24.800 --> 00:19:26.000
Yes, on it.

00:19:30.110 --> 00:19:31.780
What are you making?

00:19:32.340 --> 00:19:33.710
I'm blooming it.

00:19:34.140 --> 00:19:36.680
You said this was just a test, so I'm keeping it simple.

00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:39.379
Ma'am, they said Mo Tae Rin has arrived.

00:19:39.380 --> 00:19:41.590
Okay, go and say your hellos.

00:19:44.620 --> 00:19:46.559
Hello. Hi, everyone.

00:19:46.560 --> 00:19:51.429
- Hello. - Hi.

00:19:51.430 --> 00:19:53.830
- Hello. - Hey.

00:19:54.330 --> 00:19:55.600
Hello.

00:19:56.170 --> 00:19:57.270
What?

00:19:57.830 --> 00:19:59.600
You two should be saying hi to each other.

00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:02.210
Weren't you two the national siblings?

00:20:02.970 --> 00:20:05.580
We have the National Little Sister, Mo Tae Rin.

00:20:06.010 --> 00:20:08.410
And the National Little Brother, Sunwoo Hae.

00:20:09.050 --> 00:20:10.780
Your characters' names were Beat and Bebop, was it?

00:20:11.250 --> 00:20:12.349
What?

00:20:12.350 --> 00:20:13.480
Wait, you're Bebop?

00:20:18.090 --> 00:20:19.189
What happened to you?

00:20:19.190 --> 00:20:20.919
What's that supposed to mean?

00:20:20.920 --> 00:20:23.889
I just meant you've grown so much, I almost didn't recognise you.

00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:27.130
Well, you should have just said that, then.

00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:30.270
Your personality hasn't changed a bit, though.

00:20:33.270 --> 00:20:34.270
What?

00:20:34.370 --> 00:20:35.410
Hey, Bebop.

00:20:37.610 --> 00:20:38.740
A bit informal, aren't we?

00:20:42.210 --> 00:20:43.280
Hey, Beat.

00:20:44.250 --> 00:20:45.380
Hey!

00:20:46.550 --> 00:20:49.790
The TV stars from my childhood are right here in front of me.

00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:51.250
I knew it.

00:20:51.920 --> 00:20:54.690
This is so moving.

00:20:56.230 --> 00:20:57.430
Wait, are these artificial?

00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:01.469
They're real flowers, preserved and dyed so they won't wilt.

00:21:01.470 --> 00:21:02.530
Oh, I see.

00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:05.340
Is that why they're so expensive? Counting the labour and all.

00:21:06.070 --> 00:21:08.540
Well, it can't be cheap if it's made to last forever.

00:21:08.840 --> 00:21:09.910
Right.

00:21:14.080 --> 00:21:15.410
- Je Yeon, I... - Yes.

00:21:17.980 --> 00:21:19.750
She's scary sometimes.

00:21:24.990 --> 00:21:26.960
I figured you might be thirsty.

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:40.499
By any chance,

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:43.170
do any of your customers recognise you?

00:21:43.610 --> 00:21:45.710
Because I recognised you right away.

00:21:46.380 --> 00:21:47.510
But you didn't recognise me.

00:21:49.180 --> 00:21:51.480
Should we try it before the first shoot?

00:21:53.120 --> 00:21:55.190
Could I just ask you for one favour?

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:57.119
- Sorry? - Oh, it's just...

00:21:57.120 --> 00:21:59.089
You could just stroll in like a customer...

00:21:59.090 --> 00:22:00.960
- and act shy when you see him. - Right.

00:22:01.220 --> 00:22:04.530
You're not quite sure if it's him, and you're all... You know?

00:22:05.730 --> 00:22:07.999
I just can't, for the life of me,

00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:09.570
bring myself to act shy in front of him.

00:22:12.200 --> 00:22:13.540
Just try to act shy.

00:22:14.570 --> 00:22:15.670
I'll play along.

00:22:20.740 --> 00:22:21.750
Oh, it's Bebop.

00:22:23.250 --> 00:22:24.679
Wait. Bebop...

00:22:24.680 --> 00:22:26.120
Sorry, let me try that again.

00:22:26.450 --> 00:22:27.880
You're Bebop, right?

00:22:31.090 --> 00:22:32.490
You are Bebop, aren't you?

00:22:36.490 --> 00:22:38.400
Even if I was, you're making me not want to say so.

00:22:39.160 --> 00:22:42.170
Okay, let me try again with a little more feeling.

00:22:42.500 --> 00:22:44.200
Wait a second. Aren't you the child actor, Sunwoo Hae?

00:22:44.330 --> 00:22:46.040
But you already knew I was here when you walked in.

00:22:52.440 --> 00:22:53.910
Oh, my goodness.

00:22:54.310 --> 00:22:56.450
Oh, my gosh, it is you. It really is.

00:22:57.050 --> 00:22:59.050
The youngest-ever Best Actor Award winner!

00:22:59.520 --> 00:23:00.520
Oh, my.

00:23:01.490 --> 00:23:03.719
Gosh, so if you just add "Oh, my,"

00:23:03.720 --> 00:23:04.890
it makes you all shy all of a sudden?

00:23:05.660 --> 00:23:08.529
You said you'd play along. Why aren't you, sir?

00:23:08.530 --> 00:23:10.229
It's not as easy as it looks.

00:23:10.230 --> 00:23:11.699
I mean, besides, in this situation,

00:23:11.700 --> 00:23:13.530
wouldn't our Tae Rin be the one people notice first?

00:23:14.530 --> 00:23:15.630
Actually, never mind.

00:23:16.070 --> 00:23:17.769
I guess I'm too big for my britches.

00:23:17.770 --> 00:23:18.800
I used to do it all and not complain.

00:23:19.200 --> 00:23:20.899
I'll try again and do it right.

00:23:20.900 --> 00:23:21.910
No.

00:23:23.040 --> 00:23:24.310
We're better off cutting this.

00:23:26.680 --> 00:23:27.910
How humiliating.

00:23:29.480 --> 00:23:30.810
One, two, three!

00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:32.450
Action!

00:23:34.150 --> 00:23:36.249
- Tear this open, Tae Rin. - Okay.

00:23:36.250 --> 00:23:38.160
- Then pour it in here. - Okay.

00:23:49.530 --> 00:23:50.800
That's it.

00:23:51.700 --> 00:23:52.800
Just mix it together.

00:23:53.700 --> 00:23:54.970
There you go. You're doing great.

00:23:55.470 --> 00:23:57.910
Of course, I am. This part's a piece of cake.

00:24:00.040 --> 00:24:01.950
- All right, keep stirring. - Okay.

00:24:17.730 --> 00:24:18.960
Okay, now take that out.

00:24:19.900 --> 00:24:22.230
Take it out like this.

00:24:23.570 --> 00:24:24.600
Okay.

00:24:24.940 --> 00:24:26.669
Break it up and mix it in together.

00:24:26.670 --> 00:24:27.670
Okay.

00:25:21.760 --> 00:25:22.960
Hey, Sunwoo Hae.

00:25:29.470 --> 00:25:30.700
Hey, Sunwoo Hae.

00:25:35.770 --> 00:25:36.940
Are you okay?

00:25:41.510 --> 00:25:42.510
I'm fine.

00:25:43.350 --> 00:25:44.480
Oh, good.

00:25:45.080 --> 00:25:47.219
Try not to look directly into the camera.

00:25:47.220 --> 00:25:50.920
If you can, try to look off to the side like that.

00:25:51.250 --> 00:25:52.320
Got it.

00:25:56.190 --> 00:25:58.530
- Great work. - Great work.

00:25:59.630 --> 00:26:02.829
You all should hang out when you have time.

00:26:02.830 --> 00:26:04.230
It'll make for a better final product.

00:26:04.630 --> 00:26:06.769
The bickering between Beat and Bebop...

00:26:06.770 --> 00:26:08.439
I'm sure tons of people want to see that.

00:26:08.440 --> 00:26:10.970
Then let's go to Geon No's place. The one we went to last time.

00:26:14.680 --> 00:26:18.109
Oh, we have a night scene to shoot, so we have to get to the set...

00:26:18.110 --> 00:26:19.120
I see.

00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:21.450
Well, that's a shame. Let's just drop him off on our way.

00:26:22.520 --> 00:26:23.920
That's okay, right?

00:26:24.420 --> 00:26:26.519
- Get home safe. - Okay, great work today.

00:26:26.520 --> 00:26:28.459
- Great work. - Great work.

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:29.460
Good job.

00:26:30.560 --> 00:26:32.160
Yes, get home safe.

00:26:39.040 --> 00:26:40.040
Hey, Sunwoo Hae.

00:26:40.440 --> 00:26:42.570
Are you really going to talk about personal stuff like that?

00:26:43.170 --> 00:26:45.109
What were you thinking, saying, "The place we went to last time?"

00:26:45.110 --> 00:26:47.280
Oh, so that was personal?

00:26:48.010 --> 00:26:50.450
My mistake. I thought it was official business.

00:26:51.750 --> 00:26:55.590
I heard you were in the same class. You must have been really close.

00:26:58.420 --> 00:26:59.519
Were we?

00:26:59.520 --> 00:27:01.559
I don't know. I don't remember.

00:27:01.560 --> 00:27:03.029
What's the definition of "close" anyway?

00:27:03.030 --> 00:27:04.959
I don't know. In my book, we weren't.

00:27:04.960 --> 00:27:07.259
I asked Mo Tae Rin, you know. You said you don't remember.

00:27:07.260 --> 00:27:08.900
I don't!

00:27:09.600 --> 00:27:10.600
Right.

00:27:12.270 --> 00:27:15.469
But when I messed up digging earlier and got dirt all over myself,

00:27:15.470 --> 00:27:16.840
didn't I look like a total idiot?

00:27:17.140 --> 00:27:18.439
Tae Rin.

00:27:18.440 --> 00:27:20.410
You have no idea how adorable you looked.

00:27:20.740 --> 00:27:22.279
You were absolutely adorable.

00:27:22.280 --> 00:27:24.880
Let's be honest. You did look kind of dumb.

00:27:25.250 --> 00:27:27.650
- Shut it. - Yes, you were the bigger idiot.

00:27:28.390 --> 00:27:29.390
Fine.

00:27:30.790 --> 00:27:32.120
It's strange, now that I think about it.

00:27:32.520 --> 00:27:35.090
How did we never once run into each other at school?

00:27:35.260 --> 00:27:36.860
I avoided you.

00:27:37.590 --> 00:27:40.360
I figured nothing good would come of being seen with you.

00:27:40.730 --> 00:27:41.830
What's that supposed to mean?

00:27:42.470 --> 00:27:43.470
What?

00:27:45.300 --> 00:27:46.500
What?

00:27:48.140 --> 00:27:49.570
I'm going to buy a shovel.

00:27:49.940 --> 00:27:53.339
I'll practice in my free time at home. I want to get good at it.

00:27:53.340 --> 00:27:54.540
At what, digging yourself into a hole?

00:27:55.680 --> 00:27:56.780
Can I swear?

00:27:57.880 --> 00:27:58.920
Go for it.

00:27:59.550 --> 00:28:00.550
I'm good at swearing now.

00:28:00.551 --> 00:28:01.950
No, don't, Tae Rin.

00:28:02.420 --> 00:28:03.620
She said not to.

00:28:04.150 --> 00:28:06.319
To think a little kid like you knows how to swear.

00:28:06.320 --> 00:28:07.989
Hey, don't egg her on.

00:28:07.990 --> 00:28:08.990
Go on.

00:28:17.030 --> 00:28:18.800
- Go on. - Bye.

00:28:22.640 --> 00:28:24.510
- Wait a second. - Okay.

00:28:25.980 --> 00:28:26.980
Hey, Sunwoo Hae.

00:28:33.320 --> 00:28:35.990
You had a panic attack earlier, didn't you?

00:28:38.320 --> 00:28:41.090
I know a psychiatrist, if you want to talk to someone.

00:28:41.390 --> 00:28:42.830
I haven't been on camera in a while.

00:28:43.530 --> 00:28:44.690
I guess I was a little rusty.

00:28:45.430 --> 00:28:46.629
I'll be more careful next time.

00:28:46.630 --> 00:28:50.530
I heard you've been turning down all your offers for TV shows.

00:28:52.370 --> 00:28:54.439
What's with the change of heart, deciding to be in this?

00:28:54.440 --> 00:28:56.409
What's with all the questions?

00:28:56.410 --> 00:28:58.480
After all that sweet-talking you did to get me to sign on?

00:28:59.880 --> 00:29:00.880
I'm leaving.

00:29:20.060 --> 00:29:23.630
Why are you writing your shop's log in my shop?

00:29:24.670 --> 00:29:26.139
I figured if I stayed to finish,

00:29:26.140 --> 00:29:28.000
they'd leave without giving me a ride.

00:29:29.140 --> 00:29:30.640
Gosh, I'm two days behind.

00:29:30.840 --> 00:29:32.540
Hey, hurry up and finish.

00:29:36.180 --> 00:29:37.180
Hey.

00:29:38.280 --> 00:29:39.920
What do you think of a guy in debt?

00:29:40.320 --> 00:29:42.219
- Is he pretty? - You could say that.

00:29:42.220 --> 00:29:43.819
- Is he young? - He's of a certain age.

00:29:43.820 --> 00:29:46.060
A pretty guy who's in debt and of a certain age.

00:29:46.390 --> 00:29:48.730
He's not my type at all. What are you getting at?

00:29:48.990 --> 00:29:50.790
Just a little self-assessment.

00:29:52.200 --> 00:29:53.200
So, what's the verdict?

00:29:54.100 --> 00:29:56.530
That firefighter with you...

00:29:56.900 --> 00:29:58.740
was our old class president, wasn't she?

00:29:59.540 --> 00:30:00.540
What's the story there?

00:30:00.940 --> 00:30:02.309
She just showed up out of the blue.

00:30:02.310 --> 00:30:05.069
And not to sell you insurance, or run some kind of scam?

00:30:05.070 --> 00:30:06.410
Like, with a pure heart?

00:30:10.280 --> 00:30:11.510
I wonder.

00:30:15.020 --> 00:30:17.920
I don't think it would have mattered what her intentions were.

00:30:18.960 --> 00:30:20.620
She was always really good to me when we were kids.

00:30:21.660 --> 00:30:24.189
If it hadn't been for Sung Je Yeon, back in high school, I would've...

00:30:24.190 --> 00:30:26.099
And who looked out for you all through high school?

00:30:26.100 --> 00:30:27.660
- Me! That's who! - Welcome.

00:30:28.060 --> 00:30:29.429
Hey, I was in the middle of talking.

00:30:29.430 --> 00:30:30.500
Welcome.

00:30:31.700 --> 00:30:33.940
A salad? Are you on a diet?

00:30:34.440 --> 00:30:35.440
Yes.

00:30:36.040 --> 00:30:39.879
The director said, "Who'd protect a big girl like you?"

00:30:39.880 --> 00:30:41.949
Gosh. That's ridiculous.

00:30:41.950 --> 00:30:44.150
Who's protecting whom? My character is the one who's dying.

00:30:44.310 --> 00:30:46.650
It is a romantic comedy, though.

00:30:47.280 --> 00:30:49.049
You guys go on and eat.

00:30:49.050 --> 00:30:50.920
You've been dragged into this diet with me.

00:30:51.150 --> 00:30:52.259
But please,

00:30:52.260 --> 00:30:55.119
eat something sinful for me. I mean something seriously decadent.

00:30:55.120 --> 00:30:57.089
The kind of thing that's so good it could kill you both.

00:30:57.090 --> 00:30:58.960
- All right, calm down. - Something like that.

00:30:59.430 --> 00:31:00.430
Here.

00:31:01.930 --> 00:31:03.030
Je Yeon.

00:31:04.600 --> 00:31:06.400
- Can I talk to you for a second? - Yes.

00:31:08.100 --> 00:31:09.670
- Keep eating. - Okay.

00:31:10.140 --> 00:31:11.140
Go on.

00:31:14.540 --> 00:31:16.180
Hey, what does Je Yeon like?

00:31:17.410 --> 00:31:18.550
Je Yeon...

00:31:19.150 --> 00:31:21.280
likes me. Why do you ask?

00:31:23.150 --> 00:31:24.320
Eat up.

00:31:27.260 --> 00:31:30.460
We're putting out a press release for the new programming schedule.

00:31:30.790 --> 00:31:33.699
- And our show is the main feature. - Oh, nice!

00:31:33.700 --> 00:31:36.400
So I have to write a quick summary and pass it along.

00:31:37.100 --> 00:31:39.969
And I'm sure they'll ask about Bebop...

00:31:39.970 --> 00:31:42.970
Oh, you'll mention Tae Rin too, right?

00:31:44.210 --> 00:31:45.710
I'll ask the PR team for materials.

00:31:45.840 --> 00:31:46.840
Oh, sure.

00:31:47.310 --> 00:31:48.949
As for Bebop,

00:31:48.950 --> 00:31:51.280
since you're close, could you get his for me?

00:31:51.350 --> 00:31:52.350
We're not close.

00:31:52.351 --> 00:31:53.680
Well, you're closer to him than I am.

00:31:56.520 --> 00:31:58.350
You know, about Bebop...

00:31:58.890 --> 00:32:00.560
I was a little worried, to be honest.

