What?

00:52:09.430 --> 00:52:10.700
Well...

00:52:11.870 --> 00:52:15.199
Hae. Let's talk inside.

00:52:15.200 --> 00:52:16.300
Come on.

00:52:21.840 --> 00:52:23.449
Well...

00:52:23.450 --> 00:52:24.450
What am I going to do?

00:52:25.450 --> 00:52:26.549
So...

00:52:26.550 --> 00:52:28.080
Oh, that's right! Geon No's mom.

00:52:28.580 --> 00:52:31.749
She babysat you when you were young, so maybe she can look after Nu Ri...

00:52:31.750 --> 00:52:33.919
She's the daughter of the woman you lived with.

00:52:33.920 --> 00:52:36.059
- You abandoned me and Mom. - I didn't abandon you...

00:52:36.060 --> 00:52:37.489
Chan, is someone here?

00:52:37.490 --> 00:52:38.760
No, no one's here!

00:52:41.300 --> 00:52:42.400
Hae is here.

00:52:44.730 --> 00:52:45.870
I hope you've been well.

00:52:46.640 --> 00:52:49.270
Could you watch my little sister just while I'm in the army?

00:52:50.170 --> 00:52:51.639
She hasn't even started school yet.

00:52:51.640 --> 00:52:52.710
Your sister?

00:52:53.880 --> 00:52:55.840
But her mother died ages ago.

00:52:59.250 --> 00:53:00.620
She's not her daughter.

00:53:02.320 --> 00:53:04.090
And I don't think this is the time for pride.

00:53:07.820 --> 00:53:09.019
Chan, deal with this.

00:53:09.020 --> 00:53:11.230
Okay, I'll handle...

00:53:16.130 --> 00:53:17.630
Why did you ask to see me?

00:53:19.940 --> 00:53:21.070
I wanted to see you.

00:53:21.840 --> 00:53:22.940
To see how you've been.

00:53:25.440 --> 00:53:26.940
You've been quite hard to reach.

00:53:27.580 --> 00:53:28.880
I was surprised you sent for me.

00:53:30.180 --> 00:53:31.450
I've been waiting a long time for this.

00:53:33.680 --> 00:53:35.650
Longer than I have? I doubt it.

00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:43.220
This is the money you gave me in high school.

00:53:44.730 --> 00:53:45.930
I put it to good use.

00:53:52.730 --> 00:53:56.040
If I were that strapped for cash, I wouldn't have paid off the debt.

00:53:56.870 --> 00:53:58.910
Don't you understand what it meant when I paid off the debt?

00:53:59.710 --> 00:54:00.910
Of course, I do.

00:54:01.640 --> 00:54:02.640
This...

00:54:03.810 --> 00:54:05.780
I wanted to clear my conscience.

00:54:07.350 --> 00:54:08.880
After all, you're the one who put up with that man.

00:54:16.460 --> 00:54:18.930
You seem to be doing quite well for yourself.

00:54:20.030 --> 00:54:21.400
No matter what you've become,

00:54:22.030 --> 00:54:24.100
to me, you're still the same 20-year-old Sunwoo Hae,

00:54:25.070 --> 00:54:26.470
a student who constantly skipped school,

00:54:26.840 --> 00:54:28.700
who's constantly in and out of motels and bars.

00:54:30.210 --> 00:54:32.240
I guess it never occurred to you to feel sorry for me.

00:54:32.640 --> 00:54:35.209
With you acting like that, how was I to find you endearing?

00:54:35.210 --> 00:54:36.710
And why shouldn't you have?

00:54:38.150 --> 00:54:39.510
As for Seok Joo going off the rails,

00:54:40.180 --> 00:54:42.350
it's much more convenient for you to blame it all on me, isn't it?

00:54:44.390 --> 00:54:45.989
Seok Joo went ahead...

00:54:45.990 --> 00:54:48.419
and brought home your sister, who could as well be your daughter.

00:54:48.420 --> 00:54:50.360
- And I even gave her a room. - That's my point.

00:54:51.160 --> 00:54:53.329
That's why I'm good to Seok Joo. To repay you for that.

00:54:53.330 --> 00:54:56.930
You were the right age to have her, weren't you?

00:54:57.570 --> 00:54:59.200
Do you get that from your mother, too?

00:54:59.900 --> 00:55:02.269
I have no idea why you suddenly felt the need to take this out on me,

00:55:02.270 --> 00:55:03.270
and I don't really care.

00:55:03.840 --> 00:55:04.970
I'm just here...

00:55:05.670 --> 00:55:08.010
to repay a debt I owe. That's all.

00:55:08.910 --> 00:55:10.080
You should go back in.

00:55:18.890 --> 00:55:20.790
Same nasty attitude as always.

00:55:32.270 --> 00:55:33.300
Welcome.

00:55:35.700 --> 00:55:38.040
Son. I started a publishing company.

00:55:38.340 --> 00:55:40.140
Here. A little something to celebrate the opening.

00:55:43.610 --> 00:55:45.280
They turned out really nice.

00:55:46.380 --> 00:55:48.850
These should probably go in the fridge...

00:55:50.290 --> 00:55:51.390
You opened it today?

00:55:51.950 --> 00:55:53.120
Three years ago today.

00:55:58.060 --> 00:55:59.160
Why are you here?

00:56:00.230 --> 00:56:02.230
I thought we were supposed to be dead to each other.

00:56:05.470 --> 00:56:06.500
Well...

00:56:08.500 --> 00:56:09.870
I saw the article.

00:56:12.310 --> 00:56:13.680
Are you really going to be on that show?

00:56:14.740 --> 00:56:16.280
I was worried.

00:56:17.350 --> 00:56:18.850
I didn't see this one coming.

00:56:19.110 --> 00:56:21.280
Of all the fallout from the article, of course, this would be part of it.

00:56:22.650 --> 00:56:24.850
If you happen to need money, I'd like to help you out...

00:56:28.960 --> 00:56:31.130
I'm just worried about you.

00:56:37.770 --> 00:56:39.499
Does that woman know you came here?

00:56:39.500 --> 00:56:40.600
I should get going.

00:56:41.700 --> 00:56:45.069
Oh, you look busy. Right, I'll get out.

00:56:45.070 --> 00:56:47.240
Just give me one rose.

00:56:48.810 --> 00:56:50.009
Just one.

00:56:50.010 --> 00:56:52.880
Usually, men only buy flowers when they've done something wrong.

00:56:53.210 --> 00:56:55.180
There are plenty of flower shops in Seoul,

00:56:55.920 --> 00:56:57.720
so go buy one somewhere else, Mr. Poet.

00:57:00.860 --> 00:57:01.960
I'll come back.

